  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nRight now mesh peer param Dhigh=12, there could be too many mesh peers per subnet on a test mainnet node\r\n\r\n<img width=\"802\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-04-26 at 09 12 03\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/234448448-bb2b9941-68a7-4643-82b4-b90c6e7fa249.png\">\r\n\r\nGossip Block process time\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1476\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-04-26 at 09 16 11\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/234449024-26cac769-35a4-4e21-ac1c-cd932e67c8d4.png\">\r\n\r\nGossip Block Received Delay\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1425\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-04-26 at 09 24 22\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/234450224-fa57bd4c-1674-4caf-9c42-0fb3e87e23e3.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\nIf we configure `network.gossipsubDHigh=9` so that there is no subnet has more than 9 mesh peers\r\n\r\n<img width=\"803\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-04-26 at 09 18 17\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/234449337-0e3f11ca-3e4f-415d-9d08-77fbd96d382d.png\">\r\n\r\nwe got better metric\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1496\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-04-26 at 09 19 56\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/234449554-35055cfd-359b-4a84-85e1-8ca78fd48991.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1419\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-04-26 at 09 24 42\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/234450269-279c1140-37ac-453b-890c-d4a4fadd9c35.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nLodestar should able to handle high number of mesh peers per spec (with Dhigh=12)\r\n",
